{{Documentation subpage}}
<!-- EDIT TEMPLATE DOCUMENTATION BELOW THIS LINE -->
{{Template shortcut|ww|weal}}
{{main|:Category:Articles with specifically marked weasel-worded phrases}}


This tag is an inline alternative to the {{tl|Weasel}} tag placed at the top of an article.
This tag will categorise tagged articles into [[:Category:Articles with weasel words]].

Note that for readers and editors seeking to improve text, this tag may be less informative than {{tl|Who}}, {{tl|Which}} and {{tl|By whom}} ([[WP:WEASEL]]).

== Usage ==
A date may be appended using:
: {{tlx|Weasel inline|<nowiki>{{subst:DATE}}</nowiki>}}
or just copy:
: {{tlx|Weasel inline|date{{=}}{{CURRENTMONTHNAME}} {{CURRENTYEAR}}}}

To highlight a particular portion of text, enclose it in the {{para|text}} parameter:

: {{tlx|Weasel inline|text{{=}}solution|date{{=}}{{CURRENTMONTHNAME}} {{CURRENTYEAR}}}}

== Template data ==

{{TemplateDataHeader}}
<templatedata>
{
	"description": "The template is used in the body of an entry to mark vague or ambiguous language that tries to pass as precise and meaningful.",
	"params": {
		"date": {
			"label": "Month and year",
			"description": "Provides the month and year of the citation request; e.g., 'January 2013', but not 'jan13'",
			"type": "string",
			"autovalue": "May 2025",
			"aliases": [
				"1"
			],
			"suggested": true
		},
		"text": {
			"label": "Applicable text",
			"description": "Highlights a particular portion of text",
			"type": "string"
		}
	}
}
</templatedata>

=== Shortcuts for this template ===
{{cot|Redirects}}
{{list redirects|{{FULLPAGENAME}}}}
{{cob}}

== See also ==
* {{tl|Weasel}} (message-box).
* {{tl|Peacock}} (message-box).


{{Inline cleanup tags}}

<includeonly>{{Sandbox other|
| <!--Please add categories below this line:-->
[[Category:Citation and verifiability maintenance templates]]
[[Category:Inline cleanup templates]]
}}</includeonly>

